## ğŸš€ Setup Instructions

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v16 or higher)
- npm or yarn

### Step 1: Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd ecommercw_website
```

### Step 2: Install Dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### Step 3: Install JSON Server Globally
```bash
npm install -g json-server
```

### Step 4: Update Database Path
Make sure your `prod.json` file has this structure:
```json
{
  "products": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "title": "Product Name",
      "price": 29990,
      "category": "Category",
      "description": "Product description",
      "image": "image-url"
    }
  ],
  "cart": []
}
```

---

## â–¶ï¸ Running the Application

### Terminal 1: Start JSON Server
```bash
cd backend/server
json-server --watch prod.json --port 7000
```
JSON Server will run on `http://localhost:7000`

### Terminal 2: Start React App
```bash
npm run dev
```
React app will run on `http://localhost:5173`

